1
00:00:06,806 --> 00:00:08,675
[ominous music]

2
00:00:08,775 --> 00:00:12,245
Our daughter, Shannon,
was on the rebound

3
00:00:12,345 --> 00:00:15,148
from a broken engagement.

4
00:00:15,248 --> 00:00:16,916
Anyway, about a
week later, she was

5
00:00:17,017 --> 00:00:20,653
invited to a friend's wedding.

6
00:00:20,754 --> 00:00:24,424
And she didn't want to go.

7
00:00:24,524 --> 00:00:26,192
I encouraged her to go.

8
00:00:26,292 --> 00:00:29,062
Well, we-- we both did.

9
00:00:29,162 --> 00:00:32,098
We thought that
she should get out.

10
00:00:32,198 --> 00:00:35,535
Might meet somebody nice.

11
00:00:35,635 --> 00:00:37,971
She met Dave.

12
00:00:38,071 --> 00:00:41,374
We know now that he
went to that reception

13
00:00:41,474 --> 00:00:44,811
with just one thing in
mind, to find someone

14
00:00:44,911 --> 00:00:48,615
to marry and then to murder.

15
00:00:48,715 --> 00:00:49,582
[jazz music]

16
00:00:49,682 --> 00:00:52,986
[chatter]

17
00:00:59,359 --> 00:01:00,260
She's a party animal.

18
00:01:00,360 --> 00:01:01,194
Definitely not your type.

19
00:01:01,294 --> 00:01:02,095
Michael!

20
00:01:02,195 --> 00:01:03,163
You did it, man.

21
00:01:03,263 --> 00:01:05,131
You actually showed
up, said the words.

22
00:01:05,231 --> 00:01:07,100
Dave, I was so nervous
standing up there

23
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:10,170
waiting for Jackie, that I could
actually feel my legs shaking.

24
00:01:10,270 --> 00:01:13,073
But when I saw her
coming down the aisle--

25
00:01:13,173 --> 00:01:15,141
is she beautiful or what?

26
00:01:15,241 --> 00:01:17,777
I just hope I can find
someone as nice as your family.

27
00:01:17,877 --> 00:01:18,711
MICHAEL: Oh.

28
00:01:18,812 --> 00:01:20,647
Um, who's Jackie talking to?

29
00:01:20,747 --> 00:01:22,015
A friend of hers.

30
00:01:22,115 --> 00:01:24,217
All I can tell you is she just
got through with a seriously

31
00:01:24,317 --> 00:01:25,852
disastrous relationship.

32
00:01:25,952 --> 00:01:27,287
She got all teary-eyed
when she saw

33
00:01:27,387 --> 00:01:28,621
Jackie in her wedding dress.

34
00:01:28,721 --> 00:01:30,056
DAVE DAVIS: What's her name?

35
00:01:30,156 --> 00:01:30,990
I'm drawing a blank.

36
00:01:31,091 --> 00:01:32,058
Oh.

37
00:01:32,158 --> 00:01:33,893
But she's a nurse
at Jackie's hospital.

38
00:01:33,993 --> 00:01:35,161
Why don't you go
back to your bride.

39
00:01:35,261 --> 00:01:36,563
Entertain your guests.
I'll mingle.

40
00:01:36,663 --> 00:01:37,564
OK.

41
00:01:47,740 --> 00:01:49,008
Want to get married?

42
00:01:49,109 --> 00:01:51,744
[chuckles] Yeah, right.

43
00:01:51,845 --> 00:01:52,679
Why not?

44
00:01:52,779 --> 00:01:54,747
The minister's already here.

45
00:01:54,848 --> 00:01:55,849
I've been watching him.

46
00:01:55,949 --> 00:01:57,150
He's had a couple of drinks.

47
00:01:57,250 --> 00:01:58,418
We might be able
to get a discount.

48
00:01:58,518 --> 00:01:59,519
Well, don't you
think we should

49
00:01:59,619 --> 00:02:00,653
get to know each other first?

50
00:02:00,753 --> 00:02:01,688
DAVE DAVIS: I think that's
a little old-fashioned,

51
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:02,689
don't you?

52
00:02:02,789 --> 00:02:04,023
Hm, I'm an old-fashioned
kind of girl.

53
00:02:04,124 --> 00:02:05,158
Then you want some champagne.

54
00:02:05,258 --> 00:02:06,159
Waiter.

55
00:02:09,295 --> 00:02:11,531
Hi, I'm Dave.

56
00:02:11,631 --> 00:02:12,732
Dave Davis.

57
00:02:12,832 --> 00:02:14,501
Well, that's easy to remember.

58
00:02:14,601 --> 00:02:17,270
Well, even when I'm drinking,
I hardly ever forget who I am.

59
00:02:17,370 --> 00:02:19,172
Who are you?

60
00:02:19,272 --> 00:02:20,406
Shannon Mohr.

61
00:02:20,507 --> 00:02:21,374
The Shannon Mohr?

62
00:02:21,474 --> 00:02:22,275
From Toledo?

63
00:02:22,375 --> 00:02:24,477
(CHUCKLING) Oh!

64
00:02:24,577 --> 00:02:27,180
You've been doing your
research, Mr. Dave Davis.

65
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:30,116
Never underestimate how
far a little information

66
00:02:30,216 --> 00:02:31,384
will get you.

67
00:02:31,484 --> 00:02:33,486
Maybe you've gone as
far as you're going.

68
00:02:33,586 --> 00:02:38,725
Well, uh, I'd like to think
we just getting started.

69
00:02:38,825 --> 00:02:41,027
Oh, I see.

70
00:02:41,127 --> 00:02:42,695
So start by telling
me about you.

71
00:02:42,795 --> 00:02:44,297
[scoffs] My story
is too long a story.

72
00:02:44,397 --> 00:02:45,331
I'd much rather talk about you.

73
00:02:45,431 --> 00:02:48,001
Oh, isn't there
a short version?

74
00:02:48,101 --> 00:02:49,402
Short version.

75
00:02:49,502 --> 00:02:56,176
Well, first thing I remember is
being in an orphanage in Texas

76
00:02:56,276 --> 00:02:59,112
with a bunch of French
nuns, can you believe it?

77
00:02:59,212 --> 00:03:00,213
Not really.

78
00:03:00,313 --> 00:03:01,748
It's the truth, actually.

79
00:03:01,848 --> 00:03:03,583
Then I went to play football
with Bo Schembechler

80
00:03:03,683 --> 00:03:05,018
at the University of Michigan.

81
00:03:05,118 --> 00:03:06,986
I actually went
to the Rose Bowl.

82
00:03:07,086 --> 00:03:08,188
I'll buy that.

83
00:03:08,288 --> 00:03:09,889
A couple of tours.

84
00:03:09,989 --> 00:03:12,058
Vietnam.

85
00:03:12,158 --> 00:03:13,226
What do you do now?

86
00:03:13,326 --> 00:03:15,929
I'm just a rich old farmer.

87
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:18,097
At least nobody
shot at me, lately.

88
00:03:18,198 --> 00:03:20,633
My god, you were shot?

89
00:03:20,733 --> 00:03:21,935
Not just once.

90
00:03:22,035 --> 00:03:24,304
What happened?

91
00:03:24,404 --> 00:03:26,105
That's the long version.

92
00:03:26,206 --> 00:03:27,240
Come on, let's dance.

93
00:03:31,211 --> 00:03:34,714
[sultry music]

94
00:04:59,999 --> 00:05:00,733
Hi, Mrs. Lovetts.

95
00:05:00,833 --> 00:05:01,634
Hi

96
00:05:01,734 --> 00:05:02,735
That's a new robe, isn't it?

97
00:05:02,835 --> 00:05:05,338
Yeah, my daughter from
Tulsa gave it to me.

98
00:05:05,438 --> 00:05:07,540
She's the legal
secretary, right?

99
00:05:07,640 --> 00:05:09,042
She's she used to
want to be a lawyer.

100
00:05:09,142 --> 00:05:10,743
Now she hates them.

101
00:05:10,843 --> 00:05:11,778
You keep exercising.

102
00:05:11,878 --> 00:05:12,912
That's the key to
getting out of here.

103
00:05:13,012 --> 00:05:13,913
Thank you, dear.

104
00:05:18,751 --> 00:05:20,820
I need a kiss from
a beautiful woman.

105
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:22,922
And I'm prepared to do
anything to get one.

106
00:05:23,022 --> 00:05:25,258
Anything?

107
00:05:25,358 --> 00:05:26,159
Mm!

108
00:05:26,259 --> 00:05:29,162
That was easy.

109
00:05:29,262 --> 00:05:30,730
[clears throat]

110
00:05:30,830 --> 00:05:31,631
Jackie.

111
00:05:31,731 --> 00:05:34,033
(CHUCKLING) Oh!

112
00:05:34,133 --> 00:05:37,003
I have one more patient to
look in on before we can go.

113
00:05:37,103 --> 00:05:39,372
I'll take care of it.

114
00:05:39,472 --> 00:05:40,406
Are you sure?

115
00:05:40,506 --> 00:05:41,374
I'm a newlywed.

116
00:05:41,474 --> 00:05:42,842
I know about love.

117
00:05:42,942 --> 00:05:44,477
You go on.

118
00:05:44,577 --> 00:05:46,045
It's Mr. Chapman in 107.

119
00:05:46,145 --> 00:05:47,814
He needs his Ibgard 30
minutes before his meal.

120
00:05:47,914 --> 00:05:48,715
Sure.

121
00:05:48,815 --> 00:05:51,551
Thank you.

122
00:05:51,651 --> 00:05:54,921
Ibgard, isopropamide, the
guy's got a colon or a bladder

123
00:05:55,021 --> 00:05:57,323
kicking up that
needs calming down.

124
00:05:57,423 --> 00:05:58,424
What?

125
00:05:58,524 --> 00:06:00,360
Were you a doctor in
a previous life, too?

126
00:06:00,460 --> 00:06:01,627
Thought about it for a while.

127
00:06:01,728 --> 00:06:05,231
I studied psychopharmacology,
University of Michigan.

128
00:06:05,331 --> 00:06:06,999
Yeah, football-playing
pharmacist, that

129
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:09,302
would have been a good one.

130
00:06:09,402 --> 00:06:10,603
What are you doing?

131
00:06:13,506 --> 00:06:16,509
[gentle music]

132
00:06:16,609 --> 00:06:17,610
Does that answer
your question?

133
00:06:17,710 --> 00:06:20,446
[gentle music]

134
00:06:21,414 --> 00:06:22,448
No, we'll get caught.

135
00:06:22,548 --> 00:06:23,883
You heard what Jackie said.

136
00:06:23,983 --> 00:06:25,284
Now it's your turn.

137
00:06:28,755 --> 00:06:30,623
[kissing sounds]

138
00:06:30,723 --> 00:06:33,559
Hold on.

139
00:06:33,659 --> 00:06:35,027
Dave, I can't do this.

140
00:06:35,128 --> 00:06:37,730
You have to take chances.

141
00:06:37,830 --> 00:06:39,098
Did that the day I met you.

142
00:06:39,198 --> 00:06:42,668
[gentle music]

143
00:06:44,670 --> 00:06:46,839
Shannon, you're just glowing.

144
00:06:46,939 --> 00:06:50,710
I don't think I've seen you
like this since you and Rich.

145
00:06:50,810 --> 00:06:53,980
Actually, I don't think I've
ever seen you like this before.

146
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:56,716
Mom, that's because
Dave is fantastic.

147
00:06:56,816 --> 00:06:58,351
He's so different.

148
00:06:58,451 --> 00:07:01,154
I'm so happy for you, honey.

149
00:07:01,254 --> 00:07:02,422
You and dad like
him, don't you?

150
00:07:02,522 --> 00:07:04,991
Oh, yes, we think
Dave is just great.

151
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:07,727
And we think the two of
you are a great couple.

152
00:07:07,827 --> 00:07:09,262
You know, I don't know
what it is about him.

153
00:07:09,362 --> 00:07:12,098
He's-- he's fun and exciting.

154
00:07:12,198 --> 00:07:17,036
And when I'm with him,
everything is more--

155
00:07:17,136 --> 00:07:19,739
more whatever it is
in the first place.

156
00:07:19,839 --> 00:07:22,809
Do you love him?

157
00:07:22,909 --> 00:07:24,076
Yeah.

158
00:07:24,177 --> 00:07:26,846
I think I do, Mom.

159
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:28,247
I think you do, too.

160
00:07:28,347 --> 00:07:29,615
I mean, he's lived a life.

161
00:07:29,715 --> 00:07:32,318
You know, he's--
he's so much more

162
00:07:32,418 --> 00:07:35,788
mature and together than the
guys I've been going out with.

163
00:07:35,888 --> 00:07:38,491
Can I tell you something else?

164
00:07:38,591 --> 00:07:40,760
Of course.

165
00:07:40,860 --> 00:07:43,629
Well, not that it matters
because I would love

166
00:07:43,729 --> 00:07:47,733
him anyway, but he's rich, too.

167
00:07:47,834 --> 00:07:50,403
[laughs]

168
00:07:50,503 --> 00:07:54,540
Listen, you let this one
get away and you're nuts.

169
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:55,441
Don't worry, Mom.

170
00:07:55,541 --> 00:07:57,376
I won't.

171
00:07:57,477 --> 00:07:58,511
Oh.

172
00:07:58,611 --> 00:08:00,346
[door bell]

173
00:08:00,446 --> 00:08:03,449
Oh, he's here.

174
00:08:03,549 --> 00:08:04,650
Hey, come on in.

175
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:05,718
Thanks.

176
00:08:05,818 --> 00:08:07,053
Girls are in the kitchen.
How's the farm?

177
00:08:07,153 --> 00:08:08,221
Well, it's that
time of the year.

178
00:08:08,321 --> 00:08:09,222
It's real busy.

179
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:11,924
300 acres, 320,
but who's counting.

180
00:08:12,024 --> 00:08:13,860
[laughs]

181
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:15,795
Oh, carnations.

182
00:08:15,895 --> 00:08:16,829
They are beautiful.

183
00:08:16,929 --> 00:08:18,364
I told him if
he keeps this up,

184
00:08:18,464 --> 00:08:20,800
I'm going to have to start
buying flowers for your mother.

185
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:21,701
She deserves them.

186
00:08:21,801 --> 00:08:22,935
Hi, Mrs. Moore.

187
00:08:23,035 --> 00:08:26,172
Cille, you know me well
enough now to call me Cille,

188
00:08:26,272 --> 00:08:27,807
just like everybody else does.

189
00:08:27,907 --> 00:08:28,708
Here, let me take these.

190
00:08:28,808 --> 00:08:29,609
I'll put them in a vase.

191
00:08:29,709 --> 00:08:30,610
And you all go in sit down.

192
00:08:30,710 --> 00:08:31,611
All right.

193
00:08:34,180 --> 00:08:35,381
OK.

194
00:08:35,481 --> 00:08:36,249
Here we go.

195
00:08:36,349 --> 00:08:37,750
Oh, honey, this is delicious.

196
00:08:37,850 --> 00:08:38,918
I love this pie.

197
00:08:39,018 --> 00:08:41,020
And here's yours, darling.

198
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:43,723
Thank you.

199
00:08:43,823 --> 00:08:48,261
Ah, Shannon and I have
something to tell you.

200
00:08:48,361 --> 00:08:52,198
Well, tell away.

201
00:08:52,298 --> 00:08:54,133
I love your daughter.

202
00:08:54,233 --> 00:08:56,269
I guess you already know that.

203
00:08:56,369 --> 00:08:59,038
But the farm has a lot
of work for one man

204
00:08:59,138 --> 00:09:00,573
and with the crops
about to come in,

205
00:09:00,673 --> 00:09:04,143
it's getting harder and
harder to get into Toledo.

206
00:09:04,243 --> 00:09:09,615
It just seems the sensible thing
for us to do is to get married.

207
00:09:09,715 --> 00:09:10,616
You knew.

208
00:09:15,454 --> 00:09:18,524
Daddy, we know
it's the right thing.

209
00:09:18,624 --> 00:09:21,394
Honey, you just met not
more than two months ago.

210
00:09:21,494 --> 00:09:24,530
That's long enough to know
that I love your daughter.

211
00:09:24,630 --> 00:09:26,032
Dave, it's not long enough.

212
00:09:26,132 --> 00:09:27,567
You might be
infatuated with her,

213
00:09:27,667 --> 00:09:29,702
but you haven't known her
long enough to be in love.

214
00:09:29,802 --> 00:09:30,937
It takes time to be in love.

215
00:09:31,037 --> 00:09:32,004
Just calm down, Bob.

216
00:09:32,104 --> 00:09:33,739
You don't have to
tell me to calm down.

217
00:09:33,839 --> 00:09:35,575
Honey, we didn't
know each other very

218
00:09:35,675 --> 00:09:37,677
well before we got married.

219
00:09:37,777 --> 00:09:40,546
And that's lasted a lifetime.

220
00:09:40,646 --> 00:09:42,582
Mr. Moore, if
Shannon and I have

221
00:09:42,682 --> 00:09:45,918
half the marriage that you and
Cille have, we'll have it made.

222
00:09:46,018 --> 00:09:49,355
And I'll do everything
I can to make it happen.

223
00:09:49,455 --> 00:09:54,193
I have never in my life felt
the way I feel about Shannon.

224
00:09:54,293 --> 00:09:56,729
This is forever.

225
00:09:56,829 --> 00:09:58,664
He's right, Daddy.

226
00:09:58,764 --> 00:09:59,665
And you like Dave.

227
00:09:59,765 --> 00:10:00,833
You said so the first
day you met him.

228
00:10:00,933 --> 00:10:02,335
Why are you trying to
make him feel bad now?

229
00:10:02,435 --> 00:10:03,869
I just can't get used to it.

230
00:10:03,970 --> 00:10:05,137
That's all.

231
00:10:05,237 --> 00:10:07,273
I know, you think you're
losing Shannon, but you're not.

232
00:10:07,373 --> 00:10:08,407
We'll see you.

233
00:10:08,507 --> 00:10:09,942
We'll have you out to
the farm all the time.

234
00:10:13,412 --> 00:10:17,683
And I hope I won't embarrass
you telling you this,

235
00:10:17,783 --> 00:10:22,788
but since I lost my
father in World War II,

236
00:10:22,888 --> 00:10:25,124
I'd like you to be the
father that I never had.

237
00:10:25,224 --> 00:10:27,960
[clock ticking]

238
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:35,735
Well, you do look
happy together.

239
00:10:35,835 --> 00:10:37,903
Never happier.

240
00:10:38,004 --> 00:10:41,173
Daddy, this is what I want.

241
00:10:41,273 --> 00:10:44,410
Honey, you're a big girl.

242
00:10:44,510 --> 00:10:49,048
I guess, I should welcome
Dave to the family.

243
00:10:49,148 --> 00:10:50,349
- Thank you, sir.
- OK.

244
00:10:50,449 --> 00:10:51,417
Thank you, Daddy.

245
00:10:51,517 --> 00:10:52,418
All right.

246
00:10:55,655 --> 00:10:59,191
Well, we're going to have to
get to work on this wedding.

247
00:10:59,291 --> 00:11:01,894
Oh, we're going to save you
the trouble and the expense.

248
00:11:01,994 --> 00:11:03,362
It's no trouble.

249
00:11:03,462 --> 00:11:07,233
Mom, Dave has
always wanted to be

250
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:09,235
married in one of those
picturesque, little chapels

251
00:11:09,335 --> 00:11:11,270
in Las Vegas.

252
00:11:11,370 --> 00:11:12,705
Las Vegas?

253
00:11:12,805 --> 00:11:15,241
But how would everybody
get to Las Vegas?

254
00:11:15,341 --> 00:11:18,711
Mom, I know we've waited
all my life for this,

255
00:11:18,811 --> 00:11:21,313
but Dave and I are so in love.

256
00:11:21,414 --> 00:11:23,082
And it just feels right.

257
00:11:23,182 --> 00:11:26,886
I don't want to wait another
minute to be Shannon's husband.

258
00:11:26,986 --> 00:11:28,688
I'm sorry.

259
00:11:28,788 --> 00:11:32,425
We'll have a big
celebration when we get back.

260
00:11:32,525 --> 00:11:33,726
[slow music]

261
00:11:33,826 --> 00:11:37,396
Well, if you really
want to do this

262
00:11:37,496 --> 00:11:43,636
and if you've thought
about it, then I guess you

263
00:11:43,736 --> 00:11:44,870
better just go ahead and do it.

264
00:11:44,970 --> 00:11:47,873
[slow music]

265
00:11:47,973 --> 00:11:48,774
Thanks.

266
00:11:48,874 --> 00:11:52,311
[slow music]

267
00:11:56,215 --> 00:11:57,116
Almost there.

268
00:12:00,853 --> 00:12:03,089
How's it feel being
Mrs. Shannon Davis?

269
00:12:05,791 --> 00:12:10,596
I feel like the luckiest
girl in the world.

270
00:12:10,696 --> 00:12:14,066
How do you feel finally
getting married?

271
00:12:14,166 --> 00:12:16,035
I waited for just
the right woman.

272
00:12:16,135 --> 00:12:18,971
That's how I feel.

273
00:12:19,071 --> 00:12:20,106
Tell me about the others.

274
00:12:20,206 --> 00:12:24,810
[laughs] My life
began when I met you.

275
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:28,347
[slow music]

276
00:12:41,494 --> 00:12:46,365
This is ours, 100 acres of
prime Michigan farmland.

277
00:12:46,465 --> 00:12:47,900
I thought you said 300.

278
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,802
I did, but I'm
just farming 100.

279
00:12:49,902 --> 00:12:51,137
Dick-- Dick Britton,
my neighbor,

280
00:12:51,237 --> 00:12:53,172
I'm letting him farm the rest.

281
00:12:53,272 --> 00:12:55,841
That's what's left of the
trailer burned down last year.

282
00:12:55,941 --> 00:12:56,909
Oh, I'm sorry.

283
00:12:57,009 --> 00:12:57,877
Don't be.

284
00:12:57,977 --> 00:13:00,045
Insurance paid more
than it's worth.

285
00:13:00,112 --> 00:13:01,313
That was lucky.

286
00:13:01,413 --> 00:13:02,782
Luck had nothing
to do with it.

287
00:13:02,882 --> 00:13:04,650
I insure everything.

288
00:13:04,750 --> 00:13:07,553
The house, me, you, even the
car payments are insured.

289
00:13:07,653 --> 00:13:09,021
If something happens
to me, you won't

290
00:13:09,121 --> 00:13:11,123
have anything to worry about.

291
00:13:11,223 --> 00:13:14,560
Except I couldn't live if
something happened to you.

292
00:13:14,660 --> 00:13:15,828
Nothing's going
to happen to me.

293
00:13:15,928 --> 00:13:16,729
Guaranteed.

294
00:13:16,829 --> 00:13:19,932
[slow music]

295
00:13:53,265 --> 00:13:56,302
Be it ever so humble.

296
00:13:56,402 --> 00:13:57,736
I know, it doesn't
look like much.

297
00:14:00,239 --> 00:14:01,240
It's only temporary.

298
00:14:04,443 --> 00:14:06,645
Honey, I don't
care what it looks

299
00:14:06,745 --> 00:14:07,880
like as long as we're together.

300
00:14:07,980 --> 00:14:09,748
As soon as the
economy picks up,

301
00:14:09,849 --> 00:14:11,517
I'm going to sell some property.

302
00:14:11,617 --> 00:14:13,752
And we're going to
fix this place up.

303
00:14:13,853 --> 00:14:14,887
You know, we
could do that right

304
00:14:14,987 --> 00:14:16,856
now without spending anything.

305
00:14:16,956 --> 00:14:19,091
It's all going
to have to wait.

306
00:14:19,191 --> 00:14:20,292
I've got something for you.

307
00:14:20,392 --> 00:14:22,828
Come on.

308
00:14:22,928 --> 00:14:26,332
[slow music]

309
00:14:29,235 --> 00:14:30,302
Wow.

310
00:14:30,402 --> 00:14:31,871
I just had them delivered
before we got here.

311
00:14:31,971 --> 00:14:34,039
They're beautiful, huh?

312
00:14:34,139 --> 00:14:36,075
I don't really ride.

313
00:14:36,175 --> 00:14:37,409
Well, you will now.

314
00:14:37,509 --> 00:14:38,777
You know what they say?

315
00:14:38,878 --> 00:14:40,512
Nothing so good for
the inside of a person

316
00:14:40,613 --> 00:14:42,414
is the outside of a horse.

317
00:14:42,514 --> 00:14:43,549
Just think about it.

318
00:14:43,649 --> 00:14:45,017
Come on now.

319
00:14:45,117 --> 00:14:48,087
[slow music]

320
00:14:52,424 --> 00:14:53,225
That a girl.

321
00:14:53,325 --> 00:14:54,126
Oh, Dave.

322
00:14:54,226 --> 00:14:57,496
It's going to be OK.

323
00:14:57,596 --> 00:14:58,530
Don't worry.

324
00:14:58,631 --> 00:15:00,099
He's real gentle.
We'll take it easy.

325
00:15:00,199 --> 00:15:01,200
What do I do?

326
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:02,501
You just give him a
little kick, like this.

327
00:15:02,601 --> 00:15:05,704
[slow music]

328
00:15:08,674 --> 00:15:14,280
Well, I was Dave Davis's
neighbor, sold him his farm.

329
00:15:14,380 --> 00:15:15,180
I like Dave.

330
00:15:15,281 --> 00:15:17,283
I wanted to see him do well.

331
00:15:17,383 --> 00:15:21,287
He used to come over and
help me doing harvest time.

332
00:15:21,387 --> 00:15:23,689
Me and my wife Annie
were so happy for him

333
00:15:23,789 --> 00:15:26,358
when he brought Shannon home.

334
00:15:26,458 --> 00:15:27,927
She was a sweetest thing.

335
00:15:28,027 --> 00:15:31,096
And she loved him.

336
00:15:31,196 --> 00:15:33,866
He'd be telling
one of his stories.

337
00:15:33,966 --> 00:15:36,402
And she'd just be
hanging on every word.

338
00:15:36,502 --> 00:15:38,771
So the next thing I
know, I'm walking point

339
00:15:38,871 --> 00:15:41,240
and then, boom, landmine.

340
00:15:41,340 --> 00:15:42,508
Oh, my god, Dave.

341
00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:45,077
I saw men step on
the things, you

342
00:15:45,177 --> 00:15:46,312
couldn't even find the pieces.

343
00:15:46,412 --> 00:15:47,746
No, this is a
Viet Cong sapper.

344
00:15:47,846 --> 00:15:48,681
They had them all over.

345
00:15:48,781 --> 00:15:49,682
They're not very powerful.

346
00:15:49,782 --> 00:15:51,083
I mean they chew you
up enough though.

347
00:15:51,183 --> 00:15:52,084
I'll show you.

348
00:15:58,190 --> 00:16:00,025
Yeah, I was lucky.

349
00:16:00,092 --> 00:16:04,663
Blew me forward on my stomach.

350
00:16:04,763 --> 00:16:12,071
But Billy Gauge, though, it
went straight to his chest.

351
00:16:12,171 --> 00:16:14,707
What happened to him?

352
00:16:14,807 --> 00:16:20,145
Well, he died and right--
right there in my arms.

353
00:16:20,245 --> 00:16:21,680
So we stopped to bury him.

354
00:16:21,780 --> 00:16:24,583
About halfway through the job, I
get pinned down by sniper fire.

355
00:16:24,683 --> 00:16:26,752
The rest of my company
splits off into the jungle.

356
00:16:26,852 --> 00:16:29,722
I ended up spending the
night in that damn grave,

357
00:16:29,822 --> 00:16:32,458
right next to Billy.

358
00:16:32,558 --> 00:16:34,493
Next morning, I'm laying there.

359
00:16:34,593 --> 00:16:35,394
I'm real still.

360
00:16:35,494 --> 00:16:36,795
[intense music]

361
00:16:36,895 --> 00:16:38,630
I hear footsteps.

362
00:16:38,731 --> 00:16:40,032
I look up.

363
00:16:40,132 --> 00:16:41,500
And there's a Cong looking down.

364
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,669
And the last thing he
ever saw was me shooting

365
00:16:43,769 --> 00:16:45,604
him right between the eyes.

366
00:16:45,704 --> 00:16:47,139
Oh, my lord.

367
00:16:47,239 --> 00:16:48,140
How awful.

368
00:16:52,644 --> 00:16:54,913
Well, we're going
to play cards or what?

369
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:56,048
14 blue.
Hut.

370
00:16:56,148 --> 00:16:57,249
Hut.
Hut.

371
00:16:57,349 --> 00:16:58,083
Hut.
Hey.

372
00:16:58,183 --> 00:17:00,586
[cheerful music]

373
00:17:01,153 --> 00:17:01,954
Let's go.

374
00:17:02,054 --> 00:17:02,955
Go.

375
00:17:12,398 --> 00:17:14,566
I'm going to pull the
stuff off the barbecue now.

376
00:17:14,666 --> 00:17:15,567
OK.

377
00:17:15,667 --> 00:17:17,369
Hey, guys, we're
getting ready to eat.

378
00:17:17,469 --> 00:17:18,303
OK.
Last play.

379
00:17:18,404 --> 00:17:19,304
Last play.

380
00:17:23,075 --> 00:17:24,443
14, 33.

381
00:17:24,543 --> 00:17:25,344
Hut.

382
00:17:25,444 --> 00:17:26,245
Hut.

383
00:17:26,345 --> 00:17:28,213
Hut.

384
00:17:28,313 --> 00:17:29,648
Dave.

385
00:17:29,748 --> 00:17:30,649
Dave!

386
00:17:33,385 --> 00:17:35,754
The great Michigan
quarterback, Dave Davis,

387
00:17:35,854 --> 00:17:36,688
has lost his touch.

388
00:17:36,789 --> 00:17:38,624
Well, I didn't
play quarterback.

389
00:17:38,724 --> 00:17:41,126
I love you anyway.

390
00:17:41,226 --> 00:17:43,295
I'm gonna see if your
dad needs any help, OK?

391
00:17:43,395 --> 00:17:44,196
OK, sweetie.

392
00:17:44,296 --> 00:17:46,532
Shannon, honey,
would you go get

393
00:17:46,632 --> 00:17:48,634
the potato salad out of the
refrigerator for me, please?

394
00:17:48,734 --> 00:17:50,169
Yeah.

395
00:17:50,269 --> 00:17:51,370
Isn't he neat, Mom?

396
00:17:51,470 --> 00:17:52,271
He's neat.

397
00:17:52,371 --> 00:17:53,272
He's neat.

398
00:17:56,141 --> 00:17:57,276
I'll carry the drinks.

399
00:17:57,376 --> 00:17:58,377
Oh, thanks.

400
00:17:58,477 --> 00:18:00,012
It's so good to see
you and Dave so happy.

401
00:18:00,079 --> 00:18:03,749
It never felt that way when
Alana and the kids lived here.

402
00:18:03,849 --> 00:18:04,817
Alana?

403
00:18:04,917 --> 00:18:07,152
Yeah, Dave's first wife.

404
00:18:07,252 --> 00:18:08,187
You knew, didn't you?

405
00:18:10,889 --> 00:18:12,124
Oh, yeah, I knew.

406
00:18:12,224 --> 00:18:14,193
I'd forgotten her name.

407
00:18:14,293 --> 00:18:16,428
That's all.

408
00:18:16,528 --> 00:18:18,197
Oh.

409
00:18:18,297 --> 00:18:19,832
[chatter]

410
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:22,301
Yeah?

411
00:18:22,401 --> 00:18:23,502
Well, you did pretty well.

412
00:18:23,602 --> 00:18:24,837
Yeah.
- First time?

413
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:26,071
No.
No.

414
00:18:26,171 --> 00:18:27,206
I haven't played in a while.

415
00:18:27,306 --> 00:18:30,275
I visited Dave and
Shannon on the farm a lot.

416
00:18:30,375 --> 00:18:35,013
I remember, on my last visit,
it was really weird because

417
00:18:35,114 --> 00:18:37,082
Shannon took me up to her room.

418
00:18:37,182 --> 00:18:39,184
And she told me
that before I make

419
00:18:39,284 --> 00:18:43,288
a commitment to someone to be
sure to ask a lot of questions.

420
00:18:43,388 --> 00:18:46,692
She told me not to
be gun shy, to ask

421
00:18:46,792 --> 00:18:54,399
about extramarital affairs,
previous wives, everything.

422
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:56,535
We were alone five
minutes before Dave

423
00:18:56,635 --> 00:19:00,005
knocked on the door telling
us to get back to the party.

424
00:19:00,038 --> 00:19:01,240
And she never
brought it up again.

425
00:19:15,420 --> 00:19:17,256
Dick and I are going to
take his tractor over to--

426
00:19:19,825 --> 00:19:20,626
what's wrong?

427
00:19:20,726 --> 00:19:23,762
These aren't mine.

428
00:19:23,862 --> 00:19:26,932
Well, they're sure
as hell not mine.

429
00:19:27,032 --> 00:19:29,902
I want an answer, Dave.

430
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:31,103
Well, I must--

431
00:19:31,203 --> 00:19:32,471
I must have brought them
home from the laundromat,

432
00:19:32,571 --> 00:19:33,872
thinking-- thinking
that they were yours.

433
00:19:33,972 --> 00:19:34,873
Are they Alana's?

434
00:19:38,577 --> 00:19:40,245
You have children,
too, don't you?

435
00:19:44,249 --> 00:19:45,150
Honey--

436
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:46,051
Don't.

437
00:19:46,151 --> 00:19:48,053
Just don't.

438
00:19:48,153 --> 00:19:49,321
How could you?

439
00:19:59,198 --> 00:20:02,301
I didn't want you to know.

440
00:20:02,401 --> 00:20:08,307
The way I feel is that you're
the only woman in the world.

441
00:20:08,407 --> 00:20:09,274
She didn't exist.

442
00:20:09,374 --> 00:20:12,878
That is not your
decision to make.

443
00:20:12,978 --> 00:20:14,146
Well, I'm not perfect.

444
00:20:19,918 --> 00:20:21,486
I want to know about her.

445
00:20:27,492 --> 00:20:29,161
She got pregnant.

446
00:20:29,261 --> 00:20:32,364
We were only
married a few years.

447
00:20:32,464 --> 00:20:33,632
We were never in love.

448
00:20:33,732 --> 00:20:34,566
But you have children.

449
00:20:34,666 --> 00:20:35,801
And you never see them.

450
00:20:35,901 --> 00:20:37,569
She won't let me.

451
00:20:37,669 --> 00:20:39,304
She told the judge a
bunch of lies about me.

452
00:20:39,404 --> 00:20:41,506
But you never talk about them.

453
00:20:41,607 --> 00:20:43,175
There are no
pictures around here?

454
00:20:43,275 --> 00:20:44,943
It's just too painful.

455
00:20:45,043 --> 00:20:48,380
She already took
my kids from me.

456
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:52,150
Don't let her take
you from me, too.

457
00:20:52,251 --> 00:20:53,352
I love you.

458
00:20:53,452 --> 00:20:55,721
[slow music]

459
00:20:56,622 --> 00:20:58,223
I want to believe you.

460
00:20:58,323 --> 00:21:02,995
Then just do it
because it's the truth.

461
00:21:03,095 --> 00:21:03,996
And I adore you.

462
00:21:04,096 --> 00:21:07,532
[slow music]

463
00:21:09,968 --> 00:21:10,869
Dave, come here.

464
00:21:10,969 --> 00:21:13,905
[slow music]

465
00:21:27,653 --> 00:21:29,721
We saw a lot of
Shannon and Dave.

466
00:21:29,821 --> 00:21:31,923
Most weekends, we'd
drive out from Toledo

467
00:21:32,024 --> 00:21:33,992
and stay at the farm.

468
00:21:34,092 --> 00:21:35,827
And Dave treated
us like royalty.

469
00:21:35,927 --> 00:21:37,829
We thought he was great.

470
00:21:37,929 --> 00:21:40,365
We were so fond of him.

471
00:21:40,465 --> 00:21:44,703
Never saw them fight
until that last day.

472
00:21:44,803 --> 00:21:48,206
I knew something was wrong.

473
00:21:48,307 --> 00:21:50,442
We must have really
interfered with his plans.

474
00:22:12,164 --> 00:22:13,298
Van going to be
ready for the trip?

475
00:22:13,398 --> 00:22:14,866
Well, that's the plan.

476
00:22:14,966 --> 00:22:18,503
And I thought-- thought maybe
we'd take the horses out later.

477
00:22:18,603 --> 00:22:19,571
I don't think so.

478
00:22:19,671 --> 00:22:21,039
I just saw my folks
at the gas station.

479
00:22:21,139 --> 00:22:22,407
They're right behind me.

480
00:22:22,507 --> 00:22:26,345
Shannon, you know we've got
things to do besides entertain

481
00:22:26,445 --> 00:22:27,346
your mom and dad.

482
00:22:32,818 --> 00:22:33,919
Hamburgers OK for dinner?

483
00:22:56,141 --> 00:22:57,776
You didn't tell
me they were coming.

484
00:22:57,876 --> 00:23:00,445
You didn't tell me I had
to clear everything with you.

485
00:23:00,545 --> 00:23:02,147
Besides, you like my parents.

486
00:23:02,247 --> 00:23:04,549
Well, not every
weekend, not this weekend.

487
00:23:04,649 --> 00:23:05,851
They're only
staying one night.

488
00:23:05,951 --> 00:23:07,486
Mom's got a ceramics class
or something in the morning.

489
00:23:07,586 --> 00:23:09,287
We're trying to
leave for Florida.

490
00:23:09,388 --> 00:23:10,355
Damn!

491
00:23:10,455 --> 00:23:12,324
Exactly, which makes
this our last chance

492
00:23:12,424 --> 00:23:13,725
to see them before we go.

493
00:23:26,171 --> 00:23:26,972
Hello, Dave.

494
00:23:27,072 --> 00:23:27,973
Dave?

495
00:23:34,012 --> 00:23:34,913
I'll go find Shannon.

496
00:23:37,082 --> 00:23:37,983
OK.

497
00:23:40,385 --> 00:23:41,286
Hello?

498
00:23:45,857 --> 00:23:46,992
Shannon.

499
00:23:47,092 --> 00:23:48,760
Oh, I'm so glad you're here.

500
00:23:48,860 --> 00:23:50,595
Oh, honey.

501
00:23:50,695 --> 00:23:51,930
Honey, what's wrong?

502
00:23:52,030 --> 00:23:52,998
Nothing.

503
00:23:53,098 --> 00:23:55,801
Something's wrong, Shannon.

504
00:23:55,901 --> 00:23:57,569
Just don't go, OK?

505
00:23:57,669 --> 00:23:58,570
Oh, honey.

506
00:24:01,540 --> 00:24:05,744
Cille, I think we're
interrupting something.

507
00:24:05,844 --> 00:24:08,680
I was just explaining to Bob,
we have an awful lot of work

508
00:24:08,780 --> 00:24:10,315
to do to get ready for our trip.

509
00:24:10,415 --> 00:24:12,083
Dave, we don't even
have to stay overnight.

510
00:24:12,184 --> 00:24:14,553
Maybe we'll stay for dinner
and then be on our way.

511
00:24:14,653 --> 00:24:16,688
Maybe another weekend,
it'll be better.

512
00:24:16,788 --> 00:24:18,290
Can we take a rain check?

513
00:24:21,326 --> 00:24:24,029
I think we should
stay the night.

514
00:24:24,129 --> 00:24:27,199
It's an awful long
drive in the dark.

515
00:24:27,299 --> 00:24:29,000
Shannon and I, we
were going to take

516
00:24:29,100 --> 00:24:30,335
the horses out before dinner.

517
00:24:30,435 --> 00:24:34,372
I thought we
had so much to do.

518
00:24:34,473 --> 00:24:36,041
Shannon, I think
we need to talk?

519
00:24:38,510 --> 00:24:39,411
Do you mind?

520
00:24:42,414 --> 00:24:43,648
No, you two go ahead.

521
00:24:43,748 --> 00:24:44,649
I'll make dinner.

522
00:24:53,425 --> 00:24:54,826
Look, let's not fight.

523
00:24:54,926 --> 00:24:57,095
You've just been
acting so strange.

524
00:24:57,195 --> 00:24:59,664
Everything's a big
secret with you.

525
00:24:59,764 --> 00:25:01,266
Look, I'm still not
used to getting married.

526
00:25:01,366 --> 00:25:03,101
And I know, I've been
stressed out over this trip.

527
00:25:03,201 --> 00:25:04,569
Well, you don't have
to take it out on me.

528
00:25:04,669 --> 00:25:05,737
I don't mean to.

529
00:25:05,837 --> 00:25:08,406
All I want to do is make
things good for you.

530
00:25:08,507 --> 00:25:11,009
I'm sorry.

531
00:25:11,109 --> 00:25:13,879
I just want it the way
it was supposed to be.

532
00:25:13,979 --> 00:25:17,148
We need some time alone.

533
00:25:17,249 --> 00:25:19,084
This ride's going to be good.

534
00:25:19,184 --> 00:25:20,452
Believe me, it's
just what we need.

